Ok now I remember, the syntax you are using refers to a previous Guake version, to achieve what you want try something like this:

```json
[
    {
        "description": "List all files",
        "cmd": [
            "ls",
            "-ls"
        ]
    }
]
```

This will display a single entry named List all files that execute the command ls with -ls argument.

You can also do some command grouping under a submenu like this

```json
[
    {
        "description": "List all files",
        "cmd": [
            "ls",
            "-ls"
        ]
    },
    {
        "type": "menu",
        "description": "Remote commands",
        "items": [
            {
                "description": "ssh to host",
                "cmd": [
                    "ssh",
                    "hostname"
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
]
```

I think it would be better to add a button on the prefs.glade file that pops out a modal dialogue displaying this examples or (better) a json template to make this feature more accessible to the Guake uers, what do you think @Stibbons ?

