So as it stands today grpc is an `extra` on this library. Using this library without grpc means that the hand-written clients will work over HTTP. These versions are compatible with GAE Standard.

I know the grpc revolution is coming and essentially all generated APIs will not work without them, so I understand the desire to move toward having grpc installed by default, however, we will leave GAE standard behind.

@omaray I feel like this is ultimately your decision. If you're okay with us essentially dropping GAE standard support until the GAE team can add grpc support, then I suppose I am as well.

