@benjaoming Wondering if an approach like this might be good: https://gist.github.com/domenic/ec8b0fc8ab45f39403dd

Basically, if Travis is running a build on master, we would make it run the Javascript Docs output, and then push to a special Docs branch on github. We would then build our docs from the docs branch, not from master - but docs would always be up to date with master, but just with one extra commit added to HEAD for the JSDocs (we would do a force push every time to avoid horribly messy history).

The other alternative is to run the docs building during dev and commit the docs to the repo directly.

