I'm thinking we could have an option `--subset-axes` that takes one or more axis tags (e.g.  "wght wdth [...]"), which will be used when generating a designspace document from a glyphs source.
Only the specified axes will be kept; also, all the named instances whose location along the axes that are being dropped is different from that axis' default location, will be dropped from the designspace. This is to avoid having multiple named instances with the same location.

