@eLRuLL @baitxo: I like the idea of having `DEFAULT_CRAWLERA_HEADERS` separated from `DEFAULT_REQUEST_HEADERS`. It is a very good replacement for the spider attributes I proposed here.

**Some pros:**

- no maintenance burden when new headers are added or old ones get deprecated;
- you have the same convenience at the spider level as with attributes, via `custom_settings`;
- no need to translate header names into proper attribute names and keep a mental map of that;
- avoid mistakenly sending `X-Crawlera-*` headers when the plugin isn't enabled (comparing with `DEFAULT_REQUEST_HEADERS`);


**tl;dr:** +1 to implement `DEFAULT_CRAWLERA_HEADERS`.

