I found a regression using nested traits with same name:

```
class SomeModelFactory(factory.django.DjangoModelFactory):
    class Meta:
          model = models.SomeModel
    with_awesome_values = factory.Trait(
          some_awesome_value="4321"
    )
class MyModelFactory(factory.django.DjangoModelFactory):
    class Meta:
          model = models.MyModel
    some_model = factory.SubFactory(SomeModelFactory)
    class Params:
        with_awesome_values = factory.Trait(
             awesome_value="1234"
             some_model__with_awesome_values=True
        )
```

`factory.errors.CyclicDefinitionError: Cyclic lazy attribute definition...`

`with_awesome_values` would be defined in both but are not cyclic at all.

